text: Full Gear (2019) was a professional wrestling pay-per-view show made by All Elite Wrestling (AEW). It took place on November 9, 2019 at the Royal Farms Arena in Baltimore, Maryland. It was the first Full Gear event held by AEW. The main event saw Jon Moxley defeat Kenny Omega in an unsanctioned lights out match. All Elite Wrestling was fined $10,000 by the Maryland Athletic Commission because both Moxley and Omega bled during their Lights Out match. ==Matches== No. Results Stipulations Times 1 Dr. Britt Baker, D.M.D. defeated Bea Priestley Singles match for the NWA World Women's Championship 11:35 2 Proud and Powerful (Santana and Ortiz) defeated The Young Bucks (Matt and Nick Jackson) Tag team match 21:00 3 "Hangman" Adam Page defeated Pac Singles match 18:30 4 Shawn Spears (with Tully Blanchard) defeated Joey Janela Singles match for the AEW TNT Championship 11:45 5 SoCal Uncensored (Frankie Kazarian and Scorpio Sky) (c) defeated Lucha Brothers (Pentagón Jr. and Rey Fénix) and Private Party (Isiah Kassidy and Marq Quen) Three-way tag team match for the AEW World Tag Team Championship 13:01 6 Riho (c) defeated Emi Sakura Singles match for the AEW Women's World Championship 13:25 7 Chris Jericho (c) (with Jake Hager) defeated Cody (with MJF) Last Chance Singles match for the AEW World Championship 19:39 8 Jon Moxley defeated Kenny Omega Unsanctioned lights out match 38:45 == Footnotes == ==References== Category:2019 in sports Category:2019 in the United States Category:AEW Full Gear Category:Sports in Baltimore
